{
  "info": {
    "name": "Kiosk POS — UB Tenancy API",
    "description": "Full Postman collection for the `ub` (Kiosk POS) Spring Boot service.\n\nCovers every HTTP endpoint currently exposed in the repository:\n\n- `Super Admin / Businesses` — `/api/v1/super-admin/businesses/**` (`SUPER_ADMIN` role)\n- `Business — Me (Tenant)` — `/api/v1/businesses/me` (any authenticated tenant user, requires `X-Tenant-Id` or a mapped `Host` header)\n- `Health` — `/actuator/health` (public)\n\n## How to use\n\n1. Import this collection.\n2. (Optional) Import `ub.postman_environment.json` and select it.\n3. Start the app: `./gradlew bootRun` (defaults to `http://localhost:5050`).\n4. Run the requests in order — `Create business` captures `businessId` into a collection variable, and `Add domain` captures `domainId`.\n\n## Auth note\n\nSecurityConfig requires a bearer JWT for `/api/**` (line 103: `requestMatchers(\"/api/**\").authenticated()`), but the JWT filter is currently commented out in `SecurityConfig#securityFilterChain`. Until that filter is wired up, every `/api/**` call returns `401`. The collection-level auth here is set to Bearer using `{{accessToken}}` so it works as soon as JWT is enabled.\n\n## Variables\n\n| Variable      | Default                  | Purpose                                                            |\n|---------------|--------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| `baseUrl`     | `http://localhost:5050`  | Server origin (matches `server.port=5050` in `application.properties`) |\n| `accessToken` | (empty)                  | Bearer token sent on every `/api/**` request                       |\n| `businessId`  | (auto-filled)            | Captured from `Create business` response                           |\n| `domainId`    | (auto-filled)            | Captured from `Add domain` response                                |\n| `tenantId`    | `{{businessId}}`         | Sent as `X-Tenant-Id` header for the `Business — Me` endpoints     |\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "8f1e2c40-0d6f-4a12-9d8f-ub-tenancy-collection"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{accessToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('baseUrl')) {",
          "    pm.collectionVariables.set('baseUrl', 'http://localhost:5050');",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "pm.test('Response is JSON or empty', function () {",
          "    var ct = pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type') || '';",
          "    if (pm.response.responseSize === 0) return;",
          "    pm.expect(ct.toLowerCase()).to.match(/(application\\/json|application\\/problem\\+json)/);",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:5050", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "businessId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "domainId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "tenantId", "value": "{{businessId}}", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "description": "Public probe — bypassed in `SecurityConfig` (`/actuator/health`).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health check",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Spring Boot Actuator health endpoint. No auth required."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('status is UP', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('UP');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Super Admin — Businesses",
      "description": "Endpoints in `SuperAdminBusinessController` (`/api/v1/super-admin/businesses`).\n\nGated by `SecurityConfig`: `requestMatchers(\"/api/v1/super-admin/**\").hasRole(\"SUPER_ADMIN\")`.\nSet `accessToken` to a bearer token issued for a `SUPER_ADMIN` principal.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create business",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "{{$guid}}", "description": "Optional — allowed by CORS config, used by mutating endpoints once wired." }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Acme Kiosk Ltd\",\n  \"slug\": \"acme-kiosk\",\n  \"currency\": \"KES\",\n  \"countryCode\": \"KE\",\n  \"timezone\": \"Africa/Nairobi\",\n  \"subscriptionTier\": \"starter\",\n  \"primaryDomain\": \"acme.kioskpos.test\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/super-admin/businesses",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "super-admin", "businesses"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a new tenant (`businesses` row) and, when `primaryDomain` is set, the matching `domains` row.\n\nValidation (`CreateBusinessRequest`):\n- `name` — required, ≤ 255\n- `slug` — required, ≤ 191, regex `^[a-zA-Z0-9-]+$`\n- `currency` — exactly 3 chars (defaults to `KES` in DB)\n- `countryCode` — exactly 2 chars\n- `timezone` — ≤ 100\n- `subscriptionTier` — ≤ 64\n- `primaryDomain` — ≤ 255"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
                  "var json;",
                  "try { json = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) { json = null; }",
                  "if (json && json.id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('businessId', json.id);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('tenantId', json.id);",
                  "    pm.test('captured businessId', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(pm.collectionVariables.get('businessId')).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List businesses",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/super-admin/businesses?page=0&size=20&sort=createdAt,desc",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "super-admin", "businesses"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "size", "value": "20" },
                { "key": "sort", "value": "createdAt,desc" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns a Spring `Page<BusinessResponse>`. Standard Spring pageable params: `page`, `size`, `sort=field,(asc|desc)`."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('paged response shape', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('content');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.content).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update business",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Acme Kiosk Holdings\",\n  \"subscriptionTier\": \"growth\",\n  \"active\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/super-admin/businesses/{{businessId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "super-admin", "businesses", "{{businessId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Patches a business as super-admin. Validation (`UpdateBusinessRequest`): all fields optional; `name` ≤ 255, `subscriptionTier` ≤ 64, `active` Boolean."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List domains for business",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/super-admin/businesses/{{businessId}}/domains",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "super-admin", "businesses", "{{businessId}}", "domains"]
            },
            "description": "Returns `List<DomainResponse>` for the given business. Includes the primary domain plus any extras."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('array', function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Add domain to business",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"domain\": \"acme-extra.kioskpos.test\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/super-admin/businesses/{{businessId}}/domains",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "super-admin", "businesses", "{{businessId}}", "domains"]
            },
            "description": "Adds a non-primary domain mapping. Validation (`AddDomainRequest`): `domain` required, ≤ 255."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
                  "var json;",
                  "try { json = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) { json = null; }",
                  "if (json && json.id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('domainId', json.id);",
                  "    pm.test('captured domainId', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(pm.collectionVariables.get('domainId')).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Set primary domain",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/super-admin/businesses/{{businessId}}/domains/{{domainId}}/primary",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "super-admin", "businesses", "{{businessId}}", "domains", "{{domainId}}", "primary"]
            },
            "description": "Promotes the given domain to be the primary. The DB enforces `uq_domains_primary` so only one primary per business is possible."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('primary flag is true', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.primary).to.eql(true);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Business — Me (Tenant)",
      "description": "Endpoints in `BusinessMeController` (`/api/v1/businesses/me`).\n\nThe controller resolves the tenant in this order:\n1. Request attribute `tenant.businessId` set by `DomainBusinessResolverFilter` from the `Host` header.\n2. Fallback: the `X-Tenant-Id` request header.\n\nIf neither is present the controller returns `400 Bad Request`. For local testing on `localhost`, the domain filter intentionally short-circuits, so use the `X-Tenant-Id` header below.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get my business",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Tenant-Id", "value": "{{tenantId}}", "description": "Falls back here when no Host→business mapping exists (e.g. localhost)." }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/businesses/me",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "businesses", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the `BusinessResponse` for the current tenant."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('id matches tenantId', function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.id).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('tenantId'));",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update my business",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Tenant-Id", "value": "{{tenantId}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Acme Kiosk Holdings (renamed by tenant)\",\n  \"subscriptionTier\": \"growth\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/businesses/me",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "businesses", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Patches the tenant's own business record. Validation matches `UpdateBusinessRequest` (same as the super-admin update endpoint)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
